                </span></span></h1></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns"><div class="tei-note"><span xml:lang="en" lang="en" dir="ltr">Bishop of Tarsus who sought the return of Nestorius from exile</span><span class="tei-footnote-refs" dir="ltr" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><span class="tei-footnote-ref"><a href="#bib2447-3">3</a></span> </span></div><div style="margin:0 1em 1em; color: #999999;"><small><p><span class="srp-label"><strong>Syriaca.org URI</strong></span>: <span id="syriaca-id"><a href="http://syriaca.org/person/2447">http://syriaca.org/person/2447</a></span></p></small></div></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns" class="row"><div class="col-md-8"><div class="sources"><h3>Personal Information</h3><h4>Name variant(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> Helladius of <span class="tei-placeName"> Tarsus </span></span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/3108-20" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">
                                    Helladius </span> was male.  <a href="/3108-21" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">Severus of
                                Antioch had enmity for Dorotheus, Eutherius, Himerius and
                                Helladius. <a href="/3108-31" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Paul,
                                Dorotheus,
                                Eutherius,
                                Himerius
                            and Helladius
                            formed an alliance. <a href="/3108-33" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">
                            After the Council of Ephesus, 
                            Paul petitioned 
                            Cyril of Alexandria to grant forgiveness to 
                            Dorotheus,
                            Eutherius,
                            Himerius,
                            and Helladius. 
                            For the sake of church unity, Cyril of Alexandria agreed on the condition that they condemn
                            Nestorius.
                         <a href="/3108-35" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
